org.sd.text.radixtree
Class RadixTreeImpl<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.sd.text.radixtree.RadixTreeImpl<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
RadixTree<T>
public class RadixTreeImpl<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements RadixTree<T>

Implementation ported to use the org.sd.util.tree.Tree datastructure.

Using the Tree enables us to apply reverse operations to the radix tree, which allow us to do things like longest substring matches.

Ported from RadixTreeImpl by:

insert

public void insert(java.lang.String key,
                   T value,
                   ValueMerger<T> valueMerger,
                   ValueReplicator<T> valueReplicator)
Insert a new string key and its value to the tree. If there is already a conflicting value at the insertion point, resolve by calling the value merger function.

Specified by:
insert in interface RadixTree<T>
Parameters:
key - The string key of the object
value - The value that need to be stored corresponding to the given key.
valueMerger - The value merger to use to resolve conflicts. If null, the conflict will generate an IllegalStateException.
valueReplicator - The value replicator to use to make a duplicate of a value to place into nodes inserted for splits. If null, the same instance of value will be used. For values like Strings, using the same value instance does no harm as the string's contents are immutable. A value whose object carries state that does change (i.e. when merged,) however, must be duplicated for proper function.
